      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabi" href="/user/show/84001290-gabi">Gabi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=sff-group-shelf">sff-group-shelf</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=world-fantasy-award-nominees">world-fantasy-award-nominees</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=locus_nominees">locus_nominees</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2524368036" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5617308679440029937">3.5 stars - rounded down.<br/>&quot;The Lions of Al-Rassan&quot; I did round up because I was so invested in the characters and loved the beginning. Here it is the other way round. The slow pace combined with a - for me - not very interesting main character left me with only admiring the prose and the atmosphere Kay is creating. This alone is worth my time, no question, but for a story that long I&apos;d rather have an engaging narration as a plus. The female side characters all were much more interesting than the </span>
  <span id="freeText5617308679440029937" style="display:none">3.5 stars - rounded down.<br />"The Lions of Al-Rassan" I did round up because I was so invested in the characters and loved the beginning. Here it is the other way round. The slow pace combined with a - for me - not very interesting main character left me with only admiring the prose and the atmosphere Kay is creating. This alone is worth my time, no question, but for a story that long I'd rather have an engaging narration as a plus. The female side characters all were much more interesting than the MC and I would have wished for more 'screentime' for each of them.<br /><br />The last quarter then managed to get me emotionally involved like I wished I could have been from the start. There were some outstandingly beautifully written scenes. Yet when balanced against the whole of the book I can not give a fourth star for that. <br />Perhaps it would have worked better if some of the middle parts had been tightened.<br /><br />I still was glad to have listened to it, because Kay's prose always enchants me. But it pales in comparison to "The Lions of Al-Rassan" or especially "Tigana".</span>
  <a data-text-id="5617308679440029937" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


