    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1270782476" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1270782476" />
    <a title="Julia Sarene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1126371-julia-sarene"><img alt="Julia Sarene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590266316p2/1126371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1270782476?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julia Sarene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julia Sarene" href="/user/show/1126371-julia-sarene">Julia Sarene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1126371-julia-sarene?shelf=fantasy-no-subgenre">fantasy-no-subgenre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1126371-julia-sarene?shelf=fantasy-all-subgenres">fantasy-all-subgenres</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1270782476" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13923294651535997542">This one is really hard for me to rate.<br/>I want to give it more stars, because the book was really well written and I enjoy it! But it did have some lengthy parts now and then. In other places the story jumped right ahead, way faster than felt right. And at some points I really couldn&apos;t understand the characters actions. <br/><br/>I did really however enjoy it anyway! It didn&apos;t feel so much like fantasy (though there are ghosts, and magic), but more like an historical novel set somewhere in Asia. The worldb</span>
  <span id="freeText13923294651535997542" style="display:none">This one is really hard for me to rate.<br />I want to give it more stars, because the book was really well written and I enjoy it! But it did have some lengthy parts now and then. In other places the story jumped right ahead, way faster than felt right. And at some points I really couldn't understand the characters actions. <br /><br />I did really however enjoy it anyway! It didn't feel so much like fantasy (though there are ghosts, and magic), but more like an historical novel set somewhere in Asia. The worldbuilding was really great, and the setting felt extremely real. Sometimes it did read a bit more like a history book than fiction - so for me it wasn't balanced out perfectly. <br /><br />But still, despite these points of critique, I still really liked the book. I have always been interested in Asian culture, so that definitely have helped. <br /><br />I end up with 3,5/5 stars<br />If you like Asian culture and don't need 100% action, but good prose, this might really be a good fit!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13923294651535997542" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

